 Ngqamakwe - The Acting Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Commissioner, Maj Gen Andre Swart, on Monday expressed his appreciation for the sterling work and swift arrest made by the members of Organized Crime Unit after a business robbery that took place at Ngqamakwe Post Office on Saturday. According to the reports, two armed unidentified male suspects allegedly entered the Ngqamakwe Post Office at about 8:15 in the morning of Saturday, the 4th January 2020. "They ordered the cleaner and teller who was busy preparing the money for the day to be silent," described police spokesperson, Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana. "They then took away an undisclosed large amount of money, leaving a cleaner and teller locked in the office." Preliminary investigations by members from Organized Crime unit led to the arrest of four suspects, aged between 31 to 51, of which two are employees at the Post Office. "The alleged owner of the get away motor vehicle was among the arrested suspects together with his son, after some money was recovered from his home," he added. "The suspects were arrested on Sunday the 5th January 2020, and are expected to appear in Butterworth Magistrate soon on charges relating to a Business Robbery." Major General Swart expressed his appreciation at the work of the detectives and all other role players involved in the breakthrough. “Serious action must be taken against those who constantly rob our communities of these essential service and the law must take its course,” General Swart concluded. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 